    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "i never got around to adding this, but  for anyone interested this yields nice results. \n\n```\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom pylab import *\ndf= pd.DataFrame(rand(100))\ndf.hist()\ndef draw_describe_table(df, cellFmt ='%.1e', colWidths= [.1,.2], \n                        loc = 'center right', **kwargs):\n\n    kwargs.update({'colWidths':colWidths,'loc':loc})\n    kwargs['cellText'] = array([cellFmt%k for k in df.describe().values]).reshape(-1,1)\n    kwargs['rowLabels'] = df.describe().index.values\n    kwargs['zorder']=100 # prevents grid from drawing ontop of table\n\n    tab = table(**kwargs )\n    return tab\n\ndraw_describe_table(df)\n```\n\n![download](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/1228240/1889437/96ef3290-7a1b-11e3-9317-870ab332b4fa.png)\n"
